# Environment Variables

Copy file ini ke `.env` dan isi nilainya.

## Local Development

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

## Required Variables

### Database
```
DATABASE_URL="file:./dev.db"
```
Untuk development lokal, gunakan SQLite.
Untuk production di Cloudflare, gunakan D1 atau PostgreSQL external.

### Authentication
```
JWT_SECRET="your-super-secret-jwt-key-minimum-32-characters"
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="your-nextauth-secret-key"
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"
```

## Cloudflare Pages

Set environment variables berikut di Cloudflare Pages Settings:

1. Buka Cloudflare Dashboard
2. Pilih Workers & Pages
3. Pilih project Anda
4. Go to Settings > Environment Variables
5. Add each variable:

| Variable | Value |
|----------|-------|
| `JWT_SECRET` | Generate random string min 32 chars |
| `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` | Generate random string min 32 chars |
| `NEXTAUTH_URL` | Your Cloudflare Pages URL |

### Using D1 Database

```bash
# Install Wrangler CLI
npm install -g wrangler

# Login
wrangler login

# Create D1 database
wrangler d1 create absensi-db

# Apply migrations
wrangler d1 migrations apply absensi-db --local
wrangler d1 migrations apply absensi-db --remote
```

Update `wrangler.toml` dengan database ID.

### Using Neon PostgreSQL

1. Buat project di https://neon.tech
2. Copy connection string
3. Update `DATABASE_URL`

### Using Supabase PostgreSQL

1. Buat project di https://supabase.com
2. Go to Settings > Database
3. Copy Connection URI
4. Update `DATABASE_URL`
